      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary bench validation — hemolysis index across 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in vitro measurements conducted on a physical replica of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump at flow rates of 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min at 2500 RPM. Agreement within 12% across all operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed for all worst-case candidates.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-experimental-bench",
      "quantitativeMetric": "NIH prediction error < 12% across 5 operating points; RH < 1.0 for all cases",
      "validationStatus": "passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cpb-hemolysis-sensitivity-supplemental",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Supplemental sensitivity validation — dimensional tolerance sweep",
      "description": "A parametric sweep of impeller clearance (±0.05 mm) and volute exit angle (±2°) was executed across the 5 flow-speed combinations. Predicted hemolysis sensitivity trends were reviewed by the modeling team and found consistent with published literature expectations for centrifugal pump geometries. The analysis confirms that worst-case hemolysis occurs at low-flow, high-speed conditions. No structured experimental comparator dataset was registered for this sweep; conclusions rest on internal trend consistency and engineering judgment informed by prior CFD campaigns on similar pump architectures.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Monotonic hemolysis increase with decreasing clearance confirmed across all 5 operating points; peak NIH elevation < 18% relative to nominal geometry",
      "validationStatus": "passed"
    }
