    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. Primary validation demonstrates NIH prediction error below 15% acceptance criterion across all operating points. High assurance level declared based on the breadth of the validation campaign and the conservative bias of the hemolysis model. The supplemental sensitivity validation, while lacking a registered experimental comparator, is considered supportive evidence consistent with engineering expectations and does not undermine the primary validation finding. Decision accepted for regulatory submission.",
